Coffee Growers Co-op, Kamuela Vacuum Cooling Co-op, Hmkua Agricultural Co-op, Ho hu Energy Co-op) Technical assistance in the areas of capital access and grant and loan coaching, business and financial planning, recordkeeping, co-op leadership and management succession planning, co-op policy development, food safety, farm expansion and land access, labor transportation, farmworker housing, clean energy planning, soil health and fertility practices, plant nutrition, Pacific Island planting in commercial systems, local food sourcing, and food system development.

funding_code: HIGHER BLENDS INFRASTRUCTURE INCENTIVE PROGRAM GRANTS - MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create infrastructure to expand the sales and use of renewable fuels. Par Hawaii Refining LLC is a fuel distribution facility company. This project will consist of installing two 10,000 gallon biodiesel storage tanks, retrofitting a 9,000 bbls storage tank, and infrastructure for barging and truck loading on the islands of Hawaii and Oahu. Facility locations impacted by this grant are: Hilo and Honolulu. This project projects to increase the amount of biodiesel sold by 4,713,960 gallons per year. The purpose of this funding program is to assist owners of transportation fueling and fuel distribution facilities in activities designed to expand the sales and use of ethanol and biodiesel.

funding_code: B&I CORONAVIRUS AID, RELIEF AND ECONOMIC SECURITY ACT GUARANTEED LOANS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide CARES Act assistance for working capital for Hone Heke Corporation dba Expeditions. As the owner of five vessels, the company operates the only PUC chartered ferry service between the Islands of Maui and Lanai; which provides passenger and cargo transportation.

funding_code: HIGHER BLENDS INFRASTRUCTURE INCENTIVE PROGRAM GRANTS - MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create infrastructure to expand the sales and use of renewable fuels. Pacific Biodiesel Technologies, LLC is the owner of 10 or fewer fueling stations. This project will install six dispensers at three fueling stations located in Hawaii. Stations locations impacted by this grant are: Keaau, Waikapu, and Honolulu. This project projects to increase the amount of biodiesel sold by 5,268 gallons per year. The purpose of this funding program is to assist owners of transportation fueling and fuel distribution facilities in activities designed to expand the sales and use of ethanol and biodiesel.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: MAND. RENEW ENERFY SYSTEMS GRANTS UNDER $20,000
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Maui Tea Ventures LLC replace non-functioning batteries in an off-grid photovoltaic system with new batteries and components. Installation will restore electricity generation to replace a portion of fossil fuels used to power a propane generator that currently provides electricity to the facility the applicant uses for commercial purposes.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
naics_description: FARM LABOR CONTRACTORS AND CREW LEADERS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide working capital to a business that converts tropical fruits, herbs and root to Kombucha, a fermented tea beverage.

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase vehicles and heavy equipment to improve dirt roads to ensure safe access by staff, volunteers, researchers, and the general public to Native Hawaiian cultural sites and traditional gathering areas. Intense storms and hurricanes damaged more than six miles of dirt roads that lead to 4.5 miles of shoreline used for subsistence gathering, cultural learning, and restoration activities. This area is historically known for providing marine resources necessary for a subsistence lifestyle. Molokai Land Trust has been maintaining the access road system since 2010 through the support of multiple funders including USDA.

funding_code: DLT GRANTS - SUBSTANCE USE DISORDER - MEDICAL
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to fund the Rural Wellness Hubs program that mobilizes services in rural areas that offer in-person and telehealth services, through the development of links between community needs, services, and resources. This program also provides in-person and telehealth case management, and behavioral health services. The estimated population impacted by this project is 29,000.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a 68 kilowatt (kW) photovoltaic (PV) system generating 86785 kilowatt hour (kWh) which will replace 78 percent of energy for this Hilo, Hawaii business. The project will have a savings of $34,815 once the PV system is operational.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: MAND. RENEW ENERFY SYSTEMS GRANTS UNDER $20,000
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist farmers, ranchers, and rural small businesses in developing renewable energy systems, and in making energy-efficiency improvements to their operations. This investment will be used to help Puna Chocolate purchase and install a 21.2 kW PV system. Puna Chocolate, located Kailua-Kona, Hawaii, is a farm-to-bar chocolate manufacturing company and retail store. The system will be generating approximately 24,133 kWh per year for a cost savings of up to 74 percent in utility energy purchased.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
naics_description: OTHER FOOD CROPS GROWN UNDER COVER
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a 33.3 kilowatt (kW) photovoltaic (PV) system in Kamuela, Hawaii. Located in Waimea on the Island of Hawaii, Hawaii Farming LLC is a third generation farm that has been farming in Hawaii for two decades. This eco-friendly business uses state-of-the-art technology to grow their "Keiki Cukes" Mini Cucumbers, Long English Kamuela Cucumbers and Japanese Kamuela Cucumbers. The system size DC rating is 205.2 kW. The business estimates an average kW usage per month is 55,590 kilowatt hour (kWh), or 676,345 kWh per year. The installed PV system will cover their electricity usage up 321,300 kWh per year, which enough to power 29 homes. This is equivalent to 46 percent energy savings per year. Total project cost is estimated at $702,619 with a seven year payback.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a 14.49 kilowatt (kW) photovoltaic system generating 19826 kilowatt hour (kWh) and replacing 55 percent of energy for a business operating a cafe, manufacturer of value-added products as well as wholesaler and retailer of products in Mountain View, Hawaii. Upon completion of the project, the project will have a savings of $8,922.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist a veteran-owned family ranch operated by a husband and wife team for processing, marketing, and distribution expenses of their pastured meats for direct-to-consumer sales. The project is located in Honomu on the Big Island of Hawaii

funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to fund the construction of an elementary school utility building and middle school building to be used to store fine art materials and project-based learning supplies and used as a lanai for set design and other projects.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to bring health care via telehealth to residents and provide the opportunity to identify conditions early that might otherwise worsen into more complicated and serious problems. Since roads are often still dirt or gravel, telehealth is the most effective way to access these residents. We are hopeful that this project can be sustained and expanded to the other similar subdivisions in Puna, which share the same circumstances and challenges.

borrower_name: HAWAII OCEAN VIEW ESTATES ROAD MAINTENANCE CORPORATION
funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Construction (23)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase road maintenance machinery to replace their aging equipment for the Hawaii Ocean View Estates, a community located in the district of Kau on the Big Island of Hawaii. The community encompasses nearly 11,500 1-acre parcels covering 157 miles of roadway. HOVE Road Maintenance Corporation was founded with the mission to repair, rebuild and restore the 157 miles of roadway that had become near impassable throughout the years. This project would enable HOVE to continue its mission.

funding_code: CF TAT GRANT (SECTION 6006)
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide technical assistance to Hana Laulima Lahui O Kau (Hana Laulima), a nonprofit organization located in the community of Naalehu in the District of Kau. Changemakers will provide program development and grant writing services to Hana Laulima who has plans for a Cultural Learning Center in Kau. The Learning Center will provide services for early childhood education, culture-based education programs, afterschool and intercession programs for youth, small Business development space, incubator kitchen, cultural exhibits and demonstrations. The goal of Changemakers is to develop the capacity of Hawaiian communities, particularly in rural communities to develop essential community facilities.

funding_code: (LOAN ONLY) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to improve a 160-unit residential condominium located in the Hauula CDP, on the island of Oahu. The wastewater treatment system was built in the mid-1970s on-site and since 2017, the association has experienced numerous wastewater spill reports due to the failing treatment unit and disposal system. The proposed project involves replacing the treatment system with a new Multi-Stage Fixed Biofilm System and ultraviolet disinfection system. The collection, conveyance and disposal systems will remain in place, and will receive minor rehabilitation. This project will assist in providing the necessary improvements as required by the State of Hawaiis Department of Health and improve the health and quality of life of its residents, community and the environment.

Mao Farms plans to build a 12,000 square foot post-harvest processing facility, specifically designed to handle increased throughput. Mao Farm provides essential services to the community by producing food for the local community. Its largest community impact is from the vocational training provided to the youth. The vocational school provides a future for the youth in the surrounding rural communities. Students that participate in the vocational school learn a strong work ethic, knowledge on food production and processing, and many life skills. The Waianae Community Re-development Corporation, also known as MAO Organic Farms (MAO), is a vocational training non-profit organization that uses farming as the medium and will provide future job opportunities to high school and college students for over 20 years. Waianae Community Re-Development Corporation is a Congressionally Directed Spending (CDS) award recipient of $896,000.

funding_code: (LOAN ONLY) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace the wastewater treatment system at Pats at Punaluu, a residential 160-unit condominium community in Hauula on the northeast coast of Oahu. The property is more than four miles from the nearest municipal wastewater treatment system. The project will install multistage fixed biofilm and ultraviolet disinfection systems. System components will remain in place with rehabilitation to two of nine injection wells. The owners association has received numerous wastewater spill reports caused by failing wastewater treatment and disposal.

borrower_name: Association of Apartment Owners of Ono Vista
project_name: Rehabilitation of Existing Wastewater Effluent Disposal System
funding_code: (LOAN ONLY) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist Ono Vista. Ono Vista is a residential community situated in Waialua on the north coast of the island of Oahu. The Association of Apartment Owners is proposing to rehabilitate the residential communitys aged wastewater effluent disposal system which has been recognized by the State Department of Health with an impermissible operation and maintenance rating due to the injection wells requiring pumping five days a week. The project proposes to rehabilitate the systems three wastewater effluent injection wells which would entail re-drilling, construction, development and testing.

program: SEARCH - Special Evaluation Assistance for Rural Communities and Households Grant (WEP)
borrower_name: Association of Unit Owners of Poamoho Camp
project_name: Public Consecutive Water System Pipeline Improvements
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) SEARCH GRANTS WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment is for the Association of Poamoho Camp that owns and operates a privately owned Public Consecutive Water System Pipeline from Alii Turf to Poamoho Camp which is the original water pipeline from the 1900s. The waterline crosses over several agricultural parcels in Whitmore. For decades, the waterline has provided water to the Camp, Helemano/ORI Facility (serving individuals with disabilities) and Greenworld Coffee Farm (providing service to visitors of Wahiawa and jobs for the area locals). The waterline has experienced excessive major water leaks since 2016 which has been an incredible financial burden on the 66 residential households of Poamoho Camp.

funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
naics_description: FRUIT AND TREE NUT COMBINATION FARMING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist OK Farms LLC, a commercial agricultural production of vegetable and fruit crops farming operation in Hilo, Hawaii, install a photovoltaic (PV) renewable energy system. This project will be used for the farms washing, processing, and packing station as described in the application. The system is a Tesla Powerwall and Gateway equipment. This project is expected to save $11,215 per year. It is a new power generation system projected to have historically used 14,006 kilowatt hours (kWh) annually, which will now provide them with 23,365 kWh per year (a 166 percent annual energy replacement). This system installation will save an equivalent of 23 barrels of oil consumed, 11,322 pounds of coal burned per year, 10.1 metric tons of carbon dioxide emissions, and reduce greenhouse gases and fossil fuel emissions through carbon sequestration of 12 acres of planted trees per year.
